.\" Manpage for bitcoin-bip39(1) — BIP-39 mnemonics.
.TH BITCOIN-BIP39 1 "2026-05-21" "bitcoin 1.22.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
bitcoin\-bip39 \- BIP-39 mnemonic generation and validation

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bitcoin bip39
.RI [ options ]
.B words
.RI [ wordlist ]
.br
.B bitcoin bip39
.RI [ options ]
.B create
.RI [ "bits | ent" ]
.br
.B bitcoin bip39
.RI [ options ]
.B check
.I mnemonic
.br
.B bitcoin bip39
.RI [ options ]
.B seed
.I mnemonic
.br
.B bitcoin bip39 help
.RI [ command ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bitcoin bip39
implements the BIP-39 mnemonic specification: convert entropy to a
human-readable word sequence (and back), check that a mnemonic
has the right length and checksum, and derive the binary seed used
as input to
.BR bitcoin-bip32 (1).

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -d
Enable debug output (shell trace).
.TP
.B -q
Quiet mode (suppress info logging).
.TP
.B -p
Read a BIP-39 passphrase from the controlling terminal at seed time.
The passphrase is concatenated with the literal salt
.B "mnemonic"
per BIP-39 §From mnemonic to seed.

.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.BR "words " [ wordlist ]
Print the words of
.I wordlist
(default: English) one per line. The English list is the only one
shipped today.
.TP
.BR "create " [ "bits | ent" ]
Generate a mnemonic. Pass a bit length (one of 128, 160, 192, 224,
256) to specify entropy; pass a hex string to use that entropy
verbatim (deterministic — for tests and vectors).
.TP
.BI "check " mnemonic
Validate a mnemonic's word count (must be one of 12, 15, 18, 21,
24) and its embedded checksum. Exits 0 if valid.
.TP
.BI "seed " mnemonic
Apply PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA512 (salt =
.BR "mnemonic" + passphrase ,
2048 iterations, 64-byte output) to the mnemonic and write the
binary seed to stdout. Equivalent to piping the mnemonic into
.BR bitcoin-mnemonic-to-seed (1).

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B \(>=1
General error. Specific errors emit a
.B warn
or
.B error
line to stderr per CLAUDE.md §10.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I share/bitcoin/words/english.txt
The English BIP-39 word list shipped with the package.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B BIP39_PASSPHRASE
Non-interactive form of
.BR -p .
Used as the optional passphrase appended to the literal
.B "mnemonic"
salt during seed derivation.
.TP
.B SELF_DEBUG
Equivalent to
.BR -d .
.TP
.B SELF_QUIET
Equivalent to
.BR -q .

.SH STANDARDS
.IP \(bu 2
BIP-39 (Mnemonic code for generating deterministic keys), shipped
at
.IR share/doc/bitcoin/standards/bip-0039.mediawiki .

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bitcoin (1),
.BR bitcoin-bip32 (1),
.BR bitcoin-mnemonic-to-seed (1),
.BR bitcoin-wallet (1)

.SH HISTORY
Plugin introduced in bitcoin 1.0.0. Man page added in 1.23.0
(FEAT-041).
